                <section id="introduction">
                    <p>Basketball has undergone a revolutionary transformation in recent years, driven by the integration of advanced analytics and data science. What once relied primarily on traditional statistics and intuition now leverages sophisticated algorithms, player tracking technology, and predictive modeling to optimize every aspect of the game.</p>

                    <p>Modern basketball analytics goes far beyond simple box score statistics. Today's teams employ data scientists, statisticians, and technology specialists to extract meaningful insights from vast amounts of data collected during games and practices.</p>
