                <h2 id="evolution">The Evolution of Basketball Stats</h2>
                <p>Traditional basketball statistics focused on basic counting stats: points, rebounds, assists, steals, and blocks. While these metrics provided valuable information, they only told part of the story. The analytics revolution began with the introduction of more sophisticated metrics that better captured player and team performance.</p>

                <blockquote class="blockquote border-start border-4 ps-4 my-4" style="border-color: var(--primary-color) !important;">
