                <h2 id="technology">Technology Behind the Data</h2>
                <p>Modern basketball analytics relies on sophisticated technology to collect and process data. Camera systems, wearable sensors, and machine learning algorithms work together to capture every movement on the court.</p>

                <h3>Player Tracking Systems</h3>
                <p>NBA arenas are equipped with cameras that track player and ball movement 25 times per second. This technology captures data on speed, distance traveled, player separation, and countless other metrics that were previously impossible to measure accurately.</p>

                <h2 id="impact">Impact on Modern Basketball</h2>
                <p>The analytics revolution has fundamentally changed how basketball is played, coached, and consumed. Teams now make strategic decisions based on data-driven insights, from player acquisitions to in-game substitutions.</p>

                <div class="alert alert-info border-start border-4 ps-4" style="border-color: var(--accent-color) !important; background-color: rgba(59, 172, 182, 0.1);">
